<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:30PM CDT  by NWS Kansas City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Adair
County through 345 PM CDT...
At 330 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brashear, or 9 miles northeast of La Plata, moving northeast at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Brashear and Gibbs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for northeastern
Missouri.</instruction>
